HEADWORD: Propretor
<hw>Pro*pre"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propraetor</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> for, before + <ets>praetor</ets> a
pretor.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A magistrate who, having
been pretor at home, was appointed to the government of a
province.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>propr⟦ae⟧tor</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proprietary</ent>⟦br⟧
